Job Posting End Date
September 27, 2024
Job Location
Rutherford
Job Description
Our people share the same set of values that keep us REAL. Respect, Energy and Effort, Attitude and Leadership encapsulates what we stand for at Fulton Hogan and encourage us to foster a diverse and inclusive culture where we listen to, care for, celebrate, and respect everyone.*What’s on offer?*
Fulton Hogan is currently looking for an experienced Traffic Controller to be a part of our existing growing Traffic Control Team based out of Rutherford NSW. The role will involve working with our spray sealing crews throughout NSW. The core duty of these roles will be to work as part of a team responsible for traffic management for major road works, maintenance works and civil construction projects.*How you’ll connect to the role?** A strong focus on Traffic Management, with current relevant tickets;
* A construction induction card (Red/White Card);
* Availability to work overtime and away from home during peak maintenance periods;
* Be willing to help spray seal crew on the ground when traffic control not required or during quiet periods;
* Self-motivation with the ability to plan the day's works unsupervised;
* A strong commitment to safety;
* Have a can do attitude


The pre-employment process will involve a medical check including drug and alcohol screening and a pre-employment medical.* Want to be paid well for the Good Work you do? Apply now to learn more about the applicable hourly rate and allowances.
* Living Safely: We place people at the heart of everything we do because everyone has the right to go home safely. We have an unrelenting focus on the effective management of critical risks and take personal responsibility for keeping ourselves and others safe.
* Keen to progress your career? We invest in our people and provide career development pathways by offering apprenticeships, traineeship, and certificate(s) opportunities. If additional tickets & licenses are required, we can help with that too.
* Looking to enhance your wellbeing? We offer great benefits, including corporate health and fitness programs, health insurance discounts, personal banking support, and a range of retailer discounts. We also provide access to our Employee Assistance Program (including your immediate family).
* Want to help us better the communities we live and work in? Our purpose of *creating, connecting, and caring for communities* is more than a saying to us – it’s a way of thinking, working, and living because we're locals too, and seek to give back in ways that strengthen and build resilient communities. You’ll find us partnering with local and national community groups, like Clontarf Foundation, Black Dog Institute, and Soldier On, in addition to indigenous groups and social enterprises, to ensure that our good work positively impacts and brings about sustainable change within our industry.



If our REAL values resonate with you, please submit an application for the position. If you’re not sure that you meet 100% of the selection criteria, that’s okay, we would still like to hear from you and potentially discuss how your skills could be utilised at Fulton Hogan. *For 90 years, Fulton Hogan has been delivering high-quality infrastructure to improve the lives of people every day. Our 10,000+ team works in every kind of weather and environment, creating, connecting, and caring for communities across Australia and New Zealand.* *We celebrate and embrace diversity across our business and are committed to equal employment opportunities.**We believe in the value that diversity brings to our team and people who share our REAL values are encouraged to apply*

FlexStaff is seeking a **Grants Administrator** for **our client**, a research and education department of a higher education institution. This position is responsible for the preparation, submission, pre-award and post-award grants management of extramural grants.


**RESPONSIBILITIES**


* Responsible for working with faculty and students to prepare research grants and fellowship applications to the NIH, other federal and state agencies, public and private organizations and foundations; including but not limited to budget preparation, preparing proposal packages via Cayuse, eRA Commons, agency portals, etc.;


* Responsible for directing grant approvals through the system and subsequent electronic transmissions and manual submissions to grant-awarding agencies;


* Track grant deadlines and progress report due dates;


* Compiles and maintains detailed reports on active, submitted and pending grants; assist faculty with other support information;


* Audit monthly ledgers to determine accuracy and monitor spending activities;


* Maintains list of animal research protocols, environmental health and safety forms, etc.


* Monitors and disseminates information concerning guidelines and regulations for grant applications including eligibility, use of human subjects, animals, changes in forms, etc.;


* Works with the Department Administrator to assure customer service and smooth flow of financial data and post-award information.


* Work closely with a variety of departments including but not limited to: Research Finance; Office of Grant Support and IACUC, EH&S and IRB.


**QUALIFICATIONS**


* A BA/BS in business administration or other related field is required.


* Minimum 3-5 years prior related experience in the pre- and/or post award function, specifically with NIH.


* Experience in grant and contract financial management in a research environment is strongly preferred.
